text: Vigdís Ásgeirsdóttir (born 14 August 1977) is an Icelandic badminton player. She was the women's doubles winner in the 1995, 1996, 1999, and 2001 Iceland Internationals. She played at the 1995 IBF World Championships in the mixed doubles event with Guðmundur Adolfsson. She played in the 2015 BWF World Senior Championships with Elsa Nielsen. == References == ==Other websites== * Category:1977 births Category:Living people Category:Icelandic sportspeople Category:Badminton players
